* {{WP|Mads Mikkelsen}} as [[Kaecilius (Earth-199999)|Kaecilius]]<ref name="Stuhlbarg"/>{{r|Marvel's Doctor Strange Prelude Vol 1 1}}
** Mikkelsen is playing the main antagonist of the film. The character is "a sorcerer who breaks off into his own sect", according to Feige.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/12/28/doctor-strange-mads-mikkelsen|title=Mads Mikkelsen is playing the main villain in Marvel's Doctor Strange - exclusive|last=Collis|first=Mark|work=Entertainment Weekly|date=28 December 2015|accessdate=30 December 2015}}</ref>

* {{WP|Tilda Swinton}} as the [[Ancient One (Earth-199999)|Ancient One]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://screencrush.com/tilda-swinton-doctor-strange-interview/|title=Tilda Swinton Explains Why She's "Really, Really, Really Excited" to Star in Marvel's 'Doctor Strange'|last=Sampson|first=Mike|work=Screen Crush|date=14 July 2015|accessdate=14 July 2015}}</ref>

Additionally, Zara Phythian, Alaa Safi, and Katrina Durden portray unnamed Zealots. Topo Wresniwiro, Umit Ulgen, Linda Duan, and Mark Anthony Brighton portray Masters [[Hamir (Earth-199999)|Hamir]], [[Sol Rama (Earth-199999)|Sol Rama]], [[Tina Minoru (Earth-199999)|Tina Minoru]], and [[Daniel Drumm (Earth-199999)|Daniel Drumm]], respectively. {{WP|Meera Syal}} appears as Dr. Patel. {{WP|Amy Landecker}} was cast as Dr. Bruner in the film, but the majority of her role was eventually cut from the final version of the film.<ref name="Landecker"/><ref>{{cite web|url= http://comicbook.com/2016/11/05/odd-tale-of-amy-landeckers-role-in-marvels-doctor-strange/|title= Odd Tale Of Amy Landecker's Role In Marvel's Doctor Strange|accessdate= 2017-03-22|last= Jayson|first= Jay|date= 2016-11-05|work= ComicBook.com}}</ref> Adam Pelta-Pauls portrays Nurse Billy. Sarah Malin and Eben Young portray Dr. Garrison and Dr. Weiss, respectively. {{WP|Stan Lee}} cameos as a bus passenger. Ezra Kahn portrayed the Kamar-Taj librarian. {{WP|Pat Kiernan}} appears as himself. {{WP|Chris Hemsworth}} reprises his role as [[Thor Odinson (Earth-199999)|Thor Odinson]] in a mid-credits scene.

